<TITLE> Garment factory guard shot, money demanded </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 28 (bdnews24.com) Unknown terrorists shot and injured a security guard of a garment factory on Friday morning and demanded Tk 10 lakh. Mohammed Jalal, 38, the night guard of Loadstar Fashion Limited, was admitted to Dhaka Medical College hospital. Jalal said three to four youths shot twice at him around 6am and ran away quickly. Later, his colleagues took him to the hospital. Officer-in-charge of Kafrul Police Station Delwar Ahammed said bdnews24.com, "Initially the factory authorities could not say what caused the incident. But in the afternoon the factory officials said one Masud demanded Tk 10 lakh as extortion money over phone." "Now we are trying to identify the terrorists." 
